{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 7 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:1",
      "text": "A good name is better than precious ointment; and the day of death than the day of one’s birth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:2",
      "text": "It is better to go to the house of mourning, than to go to the house of feasting: for that is the end of all men; and the living will lay it to his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:3",
      "text": "Sorrow is better than laughter: for by the sadness of the countenance the heart is made better.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:4",
      "text": "The heart of the wise is in the house of mourning; but the heart of fools is in the house of mirth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:5",
      "text": "It is better to hear the rebuke of the wise, than for a man to hear the song of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:6",
      "text": "For as the crackling of thorns under a pot, so is the laughter of the fool: this also is vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:7",
      "text": "Surely oppression maketh a wise man mad; and a gift destroyeth the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:8",
      "text": "Better is the end of a thing than the beginning thereof: and the patient in spirit is better than the proud in spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:9",
      "text": "Be not hasty in thy spirit to be angry: for anger resteth in the bosom of fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:10",
      "text": "Say not thou, What is the cause that the former days were better than these? for thou dost not enquire wisely concerning this.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:11",
      "text": "Wisdom is good with an inheritance: and by it there is profit to them that see the sun.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:12",
      "text": "For wisdom is a defence, and money is a defence: but the excellency of knowledge is, that wisdom giveth life to them that have it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:13",
      "text": "Consider the work of God: for who can make that straight, which he hath made crooked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:14",
      "text": "In the day of prosperity be joyful, but in the day of adversity consider: God also hath set the one over against the other, to the end that man should find nothing after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:15",
      "text": "All things have I seen in the days of my vanity: there is a just man that perisheth in his righteousness, and there is a wicked man that prolongeth his life in his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:16",
      "text": "Be not righteous over much; neither make thyself over wise: why shouldest thou destroy thyself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:17",
      "text": "Be not over much wicked, neither be thou foolish: why shouldest thou die before thy time?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:18",
      "text": "It is good that thou shouldest take hold of this; yea, also from this withdraw not thine hand: for he that feareth God shall come forth of them all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:19",
      "text": "Wisdom strengtheneth the wise more than ten mighty men which are in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:20",
      "text": "For there is not a just man upon earth, that doeth good, and sinneth not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:21",
      "text": "Also take no heed unto all words that are spoken; lest thou hear thy servant curse thee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:22",
      "text": "For oftentimes also thine own heart knoweth that thou thyself likewise hast cursed others.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:23",
      "text": "All this have I proved by wisdom: I said, I will be wise; but it was far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:24",
      "text": "That which is far off, and exceeding deep, who can find it out?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:25",
      "text": "I applied mine heart to know, and to search, and to seek out wisdom, and the reason of things, and to know the wickedness of folly, even of foolishness and madness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:26",
      "text": "And I find more bitter than death the woman, whose heart is snares and nets, and her hands as bands: whoso pleaseth God shall escape from her; but the sinner shall be taken by her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:27",
      "text": "Behold, this have I found, saith the preacher, counting one by one, to find out the account:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:28",
      "text": "Which yet my soul seeketh, but I find not: one man among a thousand have I found; but a woman among all those have I not found.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:ecclesiastes.7.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 7:29",
      "text": "Lo, this only have I found, that God hath made man upright; but they have sought out many inventions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
